.TH TFCTL-FLAGS 7 "2025-09-25" "tfctl" "Miscellaneous Information"
.SH NAME
tfctl-flags \- common flags and usage patterns
.SH SYNOPSIS
Global flags and common command options.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Most commands accept the same set of global flags for output, filtering, and
formatting. Some commands also provide resource\-specific flags.
.SH GLOBAL FLAGS
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-attrs \fISPEC\fR
Attribute selection and transformation spec.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-color
Enable colored text output.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-filter \fIEXPR\fR
Filter expression(s).
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: text (default), json, raw.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-sort \fIATTRS\fR
Sort by one or more attributes (prefix with '-' for descending).
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-titles
Show column titles in text mode.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version information.
.SH COMMON RESOURCE FLAGS
.TP
.BR \-\-host \fIHOST\fR
HCP/TFE host (app.terraform.io or private TFE).
.TP
.BR \-\-org \fIORG\fR
Organization to scope queries.
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-workspace \fINAME\fR
Workspace name.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Query with JSON output
tfctl oq --output json

# Add attribute columns
tfctl wq --attrs name,terraform-version

# Filter results
tfctl oq --filter 'name@prod'
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tfctl (1),
.BR tfctl\-attrs (7),
.BR tfctl\-filters (7)